//
// test/sema/width/field_access_expr.test — field-access expression
// width fixture (T024 rollover; specs/006-m3-sema/tasks.md Phase 4a).
// Asserts the `FieldAccessExpr` for `inst.port` carries some
// `: BitVector(N)` Type suffix per `emit-ast-format.contract.md`
// Invariant 2.
//
// **Phase 3 stub note**: Phase 3's ResolutionPass currently emits a
// 1-bit Type for FieldAccessExpr because struct-instance template
// information isn't yet wired (Phase 4b T058 / S18 refines this).
// The CHECK pattern uses `BitVector({{[0-9]+}})` which accepts any
// width; once Phase 4b lands, the fixture remains green and a
// follow-up may tighten the width assertion to the exact struct-
// field width.

// RUN: printf 'module m {\n  cpu_t inst;\n  reg q = inst.port;\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK: (RegDecl {{.*}}name=q
// CHECK: (FieldAccessExpr {{.*}} : BitVector({{[0-9]+}})
